Origin
------
addhOn's cloud client began as a vendored copy of **pyhOn** by **Andre Basche**
(https://github.com/Andre0512/pyhOn), and the Home Assistant surface was informed by
**hon** (https://github.com/Andre0512/hon). Both are licensed MIT, © 2023 Andre
Basche. The vendored `_vendor/pyhon/` tree was removed at v4.0.0 and the code has been
progressively re-authored since.

Current derivation status (honest, machine-tracked)
---------------------------------------------------
Independence is verified per module by the harness in `tests/independence/`
(structural containment + provenance gates). As of this branch:

  * Genuinely re-authored: the transport modules headers.py / parse.py / tokens.py /
    values.py clear both independence gates (Gate A structure + Gate B provenance).
    The Home Assistant platform layer was assessed independent by the originality
    audit (pyhOn ships no HA layer to copy) -- note the harness gates cover the
    transport package only, not the HA layer, so that assessment is not gate-enforced.
  * STILL DERIVED from pyhOn (declared debt, marked xfail): the transport modules
    auth.py, api.py, mqtt.py, connection.py, oauth.py, device.py -- known-derived by the
    line-level provenance audit (copied literals/structure), which is the source of
    truth. Each also trips the structural tripwire (reproducing >= 50% of a pyhOn
    module's shape -- a conservative, necessary-not-sufficient signal, not the proof of
    copying). Plus the client `engine/` package (a separate, larger body of copied code
    not addressed on this branch).

Because substantial derived portions remain, the MIT requirement to retain the
original copyright notice applies to them. Until the clean-room rewrite is complete,
this NOTICE preserves that attribution.

